<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78f17ddc-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s1203"><num value="1203">§ 1203.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is authorized to be appropriated not to exceed $500,000 for the fiscal year ending <date date="1968-06-30">June 30, 1968</date>, $750,000 for the fiscal year ending <date date="1969-06-30">June 30, 1969</date>, $1,000,000 for the period beginning <date date="1969-07-01">July 1, 1969</date>, and ending <date date="1973-06-30">June 30, 1973</date>, and $400,000 for each of the fiscal years ending <date date="1974-06-30">June 30, 1974</date>, <date date="1975-06-30">June 30, 1975</date>, <date date="1976-06-30">June 30, 1976</date>, and <date date="1977-06-30">June 30, 1977</date>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78f17ddd-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/720/s3">Pub. L. 89–720, § 3</ref>, <date date="1966-11-02">Nov. 2, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/1149">80 Stat. 1149</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/91/451">Pub. L. 91–451</ref>, <date date="1970-10-14">Oct. 14, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/922">84 Stat. 922</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/92/604">Pub. L. 92–604</ref>, <date date="1972-10-31">Oct. 31, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/1493">86 Stat. 1493</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id78f17dde-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id78f17ddf-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id78f17de0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1972—<ref href="/us/pl/92/604">Pub. L. 92–604</ref> authorized appropriations of $400,000 for fiscal years ending <date date="1974-06-30">June 30, 1974</date>, 1975, 1976, and 1977.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1970—<ref href="/us/pl/91/451">Pub. L. 91–451</ref> substituted “for the period beginning <date date="1969-07-01">July 1, 1969</date>, and ending <date date="1973-06-30">June 30, 1973</date>” for “for the fiscal year ending <date date="1970-06-30">June 30, 1970</date>”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
